    <string name="tv_update_phone_flow">Phone update flow</string>
    <string name="tv_update_phone_flow_description">Use the phone to do the real setup. In ZStream on your phone, open the TV button in the top nav bar and follow the update steps there.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_same_network">Keep the phone and TV on the same Wi-Fi. If the TV is on Ethernet, that is fine as long as it is on the same local network.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_phone_instructions_title">What to do on the phone</string>
    <string name="tv_update_phone_instructions">Open ZStream on the phone, tap the TV button in the top navigation bar, and follow the in-app update instructions. This page only links to the Android settings you may need.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_wifi_settings">Wi-Fi settings</string>
    <string name="tv_update_about_build_number">About / Build number</string>
    <string name="tv_update_developer_adb_wireless">Developer options / ADB debugging / Wireless debugging</string>
    <string name="tv_update_developer_not_enabled">Developer options are not enabled on this TV.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_step_open_about">Step 1 — Open About</string>
    <string name="tv_update_open_about_description">Go to Settings → Device Preferences → About. If your TV hides it elsewhere, the buttons below jump to the right places.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_step_tap_build_number">Step 2 — Tap Build Number 7 times</string>
    <string name="tv_update_tap_build_number_description">Find the Build Number entry and tap it 7 times. You’ll see a message confirming that Developer Options are now enabled.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_step_come_back">Step 3 — Come back here</string>
    <string name="tv_update_return_description">Press Back or return to ZStream. This screen detects the change automatically.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_developer_enabled">Developer options are enabled. Turn on ADB debugging, then come back here.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_step_open_settings">Step 1 — Open the right settings page</string>
    <string name="tv_update_open_settings_description">Open Developer Options on the TV and switch on ADB debugging. The buttons below jump there directly.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_step_enable_wireless">Step 2 — Enable Wireless Debugging</string>
    <string name="tv_update_enable_wireless_description">Turn on USB Debugging, then find Wireless Debugging and enable it too. Both are needed to push the APK over Wi-Fi.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_return_adb_description">Press Back or return to ZStream. When ADB is on, this screen will confirm it and unlock the releases page.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_adb_enabled">ADB debugging is on. You did the right thing.</string>
    <string name="tv_update_next_step">Next step</string>
    <string name="tv_update_next_step_description">You can continue to the available releases page now. There you can choose the APK and install the update in the background.</string>
